se studies stretching across geophysical boundaries from Western Europe to South-East Asia, with a time span ranging from the second millennium BCE to the twentieth century CE.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Centre for the Study of Manuscript  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEducationxHistory. 0aLearning and scholarshipxHistory. 0aManuscriptsxHistory. 0aTeachingxAids and devicesxHistory. 4aAltertum. 4aHandschriften. 4aPädagogik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aManuscript studies.  aeducational practices.1 aBaldzuhn, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyer, Wiebke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrinkmann, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrinkmann, Stefanie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCiotti, Giovanni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiotti, Giovanni, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aColini, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelhey, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDepreux, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGori, Alessandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHennings, Till, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHufnagel, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarolewski, Janina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 